Now, let me tell you about fee ehna. The point system for finding a good family is actually quite amazing. It’s not the price you pay, or the construction of the house, or any of the other things you typically think a landlord would look at, but rather everything they did not do. Not saying that everything they did was illegal (is that even a thing in the U.S.?), but rather quite illegal.

Here are some highlights:

– The landlord gets the phone and internet set up, not the tenant. Sometimes at a date and time that does not coincide with the tenant’s knowledge that it will actually be coming.

– The landlord secures monthly bills for sewage, water, electricity. They also don’t necessarily provide their phone number. When you need to obtain said bills, you find out who your landlord is, call them up, and will pay to get into their building’s phone room. From here you will hand 3 boys your paper bills
